Interface Invertible<NumberConcept>

  • Type Parameters:
    NumberConcept - A reference to the Class or Interface which the inverse element will be a type of.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AdditivelyInvertible<NumberConcept>, LabeledMatrix<LabelType>, Matrix, MultiplicativelyInvertible<NumberConcept>, Ring<RingType>, Vector
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Interval, LabeledRegularMatrix, LabeledSymmetricMatrix, RegularMatrix, RegularVector, Scalar, SquareMatrix, SymmetricMatrix, Vector2D, Vector3D

    public interface Invertible<NumberConcept>
    In abstract algebra, the idea of an inverse element generalizes concepts of a negation. The inverse is an element, that can 'undo' the effect of a combination with another given element.
